path.id: From Figure 5, the trend that should be most apparent is the proportion of beef and buffalo being consumed compared to the proportion of poultry that is being consumed. Not only has consumption of beef and buffalo decreased until 2021 but it is also expected to decrease even more by 2050! On the other hand, the proportion of poultry has been increasing and is predicted to continue increasing as well. Whatâ€™s significant about this finding is that beef (which comes from cattle) are one of the most significant polluters of a greenhouse gas called methane. This gas is not as abundant as carbon dioxide however, it is much worse in terms of the effect that it has on the environment. Additionally, poultry (containing mostly chicken, ducks, turkey and geese) are one of the smallest polluters of methane. One of the reasons this is the case is because of the concerns about the consumption of too much â€œred meat.â€ This group of meat includes beef, goat and pork. These types of meat have greater amounts of saturated fats and bad cholesterol, both which if consumed too often can increase the risks of type 2 diabetes, stroke and colorectal cancer. Along with this, when compared to the price of poultry options such as chicken, these options become less desirable for many families around the world. Figure 6 considers what would happen when switching over to plant-based meat. Plant-based is considered a substitute for traditional meat because of how similar it tastes to their meat counterpart. This visualization shows the percentage of greenhouse gasses that are emitted by the plant-based versions of some of your favorite burgers. The most significant reduction of greenhouse gasses comes from consuming a plant-based beef burger as opposed to a regular beef burger. The percentages are not as high when considering other meats such as chicken and pork but we have to remember, these animals released very little greenhouse gasses into our atmosphere in the first place! Save the world by switching to these great tasting alternatives.
